  "concept": {
    "summary": "Ancient items are stronger-grade equipment pieces that unlock fixed set bonuses when multiple pieces with the same set name are equipped together.",
    "coreRules": [
      "Ancient items are stronger than normal/excellent counterparts.",
      "Every Ancient item has at least one Ancient option.",
      "Set names and set options are fixed by set family.",
      "At least two items of the same set name are required to unlock set options.",
      "Additional set options unlock as more pieces of the same set name are equipped.",
      "Players can mix different Ancient set names to activate bonuses from more than one set.",
      "Some classes may be listed as able to use a set but still cannot equip every piece because of class item restrictions, such as Magic Gladiator not using helms or Rage Fighter not using gloves."
    ]
  },
